    "description": "Address the three categories of skills required by manufacturing managers and engineers: basics, intuition, and synthesis.  Part I concentrates on basics, by providing a historical perspective and introducing traditional terms and techniques.  Part II focuses on intuition, by describing fundamental behavior of manufacturing systems.  Part III addresses synthesis, by developing a framework for integrating disparate manufacturing planning problems",
